If you are looking for a reasonably priced FANTASTIC meal in the land of overpriced tourist traps, this is your place!! We had almost everything on the menu and not one thing was bad....- The empanadas were baked perfectly with a good amount of filling in each bite.- The veggie and meat lasagnas were both good but the veggie (yes the veggie) one was the favorite - You must get the spinach ravioli with pine nuts. We mistakingly didn't order it but the owner brought us a plate to try and it was the best!!- Mozzarella salad was the perfect starter and refreshing - The mixta sauce on tagliatelle phenomPoint is....you won't have a bad meal here!
